## Limits

The concept of a **limit** is the foundation of calculus. A limit describes the value that a function approaches as the input approaches a given point. We write:

$$\lim_{x \to c} f(x) = L$$

This reads: "the limit of $f(x)$ as $x$ approaches $c$ equals $L$." The function does not need to be defined at $c$ — the limit only describes the *approach*.

